  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Marketing Executive",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in marketing, with proven hands-on execution in campaign management.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of 360° marketing strategies, including SEO/SEM, social media, email marketing, content marketing, and offline channels.</li>\n  <li>Strong written, visual, and      interpersonal communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Data-driven mindset, proficient in using tools      such as Google Analytics, Meta Business Suite, and other marketing      dashboards to guide strategic decisions.</li>\n  <li>Ability to multitask, manage      timelines, and work independently in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of basic design tools (e.g., Canva, Adobe Illustrator) is advantageous.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in the commercial  vehicle/automotive industry will be a strong plus.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Propose promotional campaigns and branding initiatives to improve vehicle utilization and brand      positioning.</li>\n  <li>Track key performance metrics (CTR, CPA, ROAS, conversions) and provide actionable insights for      continuous optimization.</li>\n  <li>Develop and manage social media content calendars to strengthen brand presence and  engagement.</li>\n  <li>Build and manage email      marketing campaigns, including customer segmentation, automated workflows, and performance reporting using platforms such as Mailchimp and SendGrid.</li>\n  <li>Update and maintain website content via CMS platforms (e.g., WordPress), ensuring SEO best practices      are applied.</li>\n  <li>Explore and implement retargeting and remarketing strategies to maximize customer acquisition and retention.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with internal teams (sales, after-sales support, operations) to ensure marketing initiatives align with business objectives.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
